---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = 'Terms & Conditions · Guiding Winds Unplug';
const description =
  'Booking, deposits, cancellation, and force majeure terms for Guiding Winds Unplug catamaran voyages.';
const updated = '2026-05-17';
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="bg-primary text-ink">
    <div class="max-w-[820px] mx-auto px-7 lg:px-0 pt-24 pb-32 lg:pt-32">
      <p class="font-label-caps uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-[0.6875rem] font-semibold text-ink-soft mb-4">
        Terms
      </p>
      <h1
        class="font-display text-ink leading-[1] tracking-[-0.025em] font-light"
        style="font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 4vw + 1rem, 3.5rem); font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 144, 'SOFT' 30, 'WONK' 0;"
      >
        Terms & conditions.
      </h1>
      <p class="font-body-sm text-[0.8125rem] text-ink-mute mt-4">Last updated {updated}</p>

      <div class="mt-12 space-y-8 font-body-lg text-[1.0625rem] leading-[1.7] text-ink-soft">
        <h2 class="font-h2 text-ink leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.02em] font-normal" style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 72;">
          Booking and deposits
        </h2>
        <p>
          A booking is confirmed when we receive a 25% deposit on the cabin
          price. The balance is due 60 days before the voyage's departure
          date. Bookings made inside the 60-day window are payable in full at
          confirmation.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-h2 text-ink leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.02em] font-normal mt-12" style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 72;">
          Cancellation
        </h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 list-disc list-outside pl-6">
          <li>
            <strong>90 or more days before departure:</strong> full refund of
            any payments made.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>89 to 45 days before departure:</strong> 50% refund.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>44 days or fewer before departure:</strong> no refund,
            but we will rebook you for any week with availability in the next
            12 months at no additional charge. We strongly recommend travel
            insurance.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="font-h2 text-ink leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.02em] font-normal mt-12" style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 72;">
          Cabin holds
        </h2>
        <p>
          We hold cabins for 72 hours without payment. The hold expires
          automatically at that point and the cabin returns to the public
          inventory. There is no penalty for not converting a hold.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-h2 text-ink leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.02em] font-normal mt-12" style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 72;">
          Weather and force majeure
        </h2>
        <p>
          Sailing routes are subject to weather. The captain may reroute,
          shorten, or extend a leg of the voyage at his sole discretion to
          ensure safety. If a tropical system, hurricane, government
          restriction, or other force majeure event forces the cancellation
          of an entire voyage, we will issue a full refund or rebook you for
          a future week of your choice. We are not responsible for
          weather-related itinerary changes that fall short of voyage
          cancellation.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-h2 text-ink leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.02em] font-normal mt-12" style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 72;">
          Guest conduct
        </h2>
        <p>
          The captain has full authority over guest conduct aboard. Behavior
          that endangers the boat, the crew, or other guests — including
          intoxication that requires intervention or aggressive disregard of
          safety briefings — is grounds for disembarkation at the next safe
          port without refund. We have not had to invoke this rule and do not
          expect to.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-h2 text-ink leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.02em] font-normal mt-12" style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 72;">
          Travel documents
        </h2>
        <p>
          Each guest is responsible for valid passports, visas, and any
          health-related entry documentation required at the embarkation
          port. We are not responsible for missed departures due to document
          issues at immigration.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-h2 text-ink leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.02em] font-normal mt-12" style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 72;">
          Insurance
        </h2>
        <p>
          We are fully insured for liability, hull, and medical evacuation
          through MarinaPro Risk Group. Our insurance does not cover guest
          trip cancellation, lost baggage, or personal medical care — for
          those, please carry travel insurance. We can refer a broker.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-h2 text-ink leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.02em] font-normal mt-12" style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 72;">
          Photography
        </h2>
        <p>
          Photos taken aboard by the captain or host may occasionally be
          used in marketing. Tell us at the start of the week if you do not
          want to appear in any image we share; we will respect that
          unconditionally.
        </p>

        <h2 class="font-h2 text-ink leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.02em] font-normal mt-12" style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 72;">
          Governing law
        </h2>
        <p>
          These terms are governed by the laws of the State of North Carolina,
          USA, the operator's place of business.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
